Class CeSecoreNameStyle

  • java.lang.Object

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    org.bouncycastle.asn1.x500.X500NameStyle
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    PrintableStringNameStyle
    public class CeSecoreNameStyle
extends org.bouncycastle.asn1.x500.style.BCStyle
    Class that determines string representations of DNs. Overrides the default BCStyle in order to: - Be consistent for all future for backwards compatibility (serialnumber) - Be able to add fields that does not (yet) exist in BC (like CABForum Jurisdiction* in BC 1.54)
    Version:
    $Id: CeSecoreNameStyle.java 26562 2017-09-16 19:07:04Z samuellb $

      • buildString

        public static String buildString​(Hashtable<org.bouncycastle.asn1.ASN1ObjectIdentifier,​String> defaultSymbols,
                                 org.bouncycastle.asn1.x500.X500Name name)
        This method is intended to be used in toString() in BCStyle classes. It is useful e.g. when the DefaultSymbols map is not the default inherited from BCStyle. It is public so it can be re-used by other classes as well (e.g. LdapNameStyle in EJBCA).
        Parameters:
        defaultSymbols - symbols
        name - Name
        Returns:
        String
